	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jun 7th 6:25 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=79670><span id= >dsavereide</span></a><br><span id=notbold>61 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>What you describe here is price fixing -- illegal in the US and many other countries. Thankfully, the sellers in EQ are not that organized. And there are plenty of those who need quick cash or simply don't have the patience to wait for the best offer. They help bring the prices down. Then there are those on the other side who &quot;got to get now&quot; who drive the prices up. Patient buyers and sellers will get the best prices.<br><br>Prices in this game are going to fluxuate because, with the exception of trade skills items, there are no costs except the time you put in. And this will be valued differently by different people. The time spent looking for the best deal may not be worth the effort for many.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
